# PDM (Peripheral Driver Module) Configuration

menuconfig PDM
	bool "PDM (Peripheral Driver Module)"
	default n
	depends on OSAL && LPF_CORE && HAL && PCONFIG
	help
	  Peripheral Driver Module provides high-level peripheral management
	  and LPF device orchestration.

	  PDM currently hosts the LPF peripheral runtime and services that are
	  integrated through one framework module boundary.

	  Architecture:
	  PDM integrates LPF Core, PCONFIG, HAL, and LPF peripheral services
	  through one framework module boundary.

	  Memory footprint: framework shell + selected peripheral services

	  Supported peripherals:
	  - MCU peripherals
	  - LED peripherals

	  Dependencies: OSAL, LPF Core, HAL, PCONFIG

	  Note: Enable OSAL, LPF Core, HAL, and PCONFIG first in
	  "Core Modules" menu.

	  Recommended: Enable for systems with peripheral management

	  If unsure, say Y.

if PDM

endif # PDM
